Winnie Madikizela-Mandela would have turned 83 today. She died in April last year. The liberation hero and ANC Women's League President is being remembered. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Winnie Madikizela-Mandela would have turned 83 on Thursday. She died in April last year. Madikizela-Mandela passed away at the Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg. READ: Winnie Madikizela-Mandela dies Her health had deteriorated over the last few years. She suffered from diabetes and underwent several major surgeries. The liberation hero and ANC Women's League President is being remembered on Thursday.